Description: A list of all the service lines the episode qualifies for as produced by the prescribed specialised services (PSS) identification tool.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Set the same as ServiceLineList in the output table of the PS tool.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Indicates whether the attendance has been identified as specialised activity as produced by the prescribed specialised services (PSS) identification tool.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: An output table of the PSS tool is looked at, and where there is a service line attached to a record (the record is directly commissioned), then NCBPST_Flag is assigned a ', otherwise '.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The grouping method used for the spell as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The grouping method used by the local payment HRG grouper for the spell. Will either be ' (procedure driven), ' (diagnosis driven), ' (multiple trauma), ' (global exception), or null.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Indicates whether the spell is a directly commissioned service using (1) the PSS identification tool. (national) and (2) locally derived direct commissioning rules.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: All records are initially set to '. Updated to ' where NCBPST_Spell_Flag is ', NCB_Final_Spell_Flag is ' and NCBPST_Spell_Service_Line is anything but 'NCBPS01C' or 'NCBPS01R'. Updated to ' when NCBPST_Spell_Flag is ', NCBFinal_Spell_Flag is ', NCBPST_Spell_ServiceLine is either 'NCBPS01C' or 'NCBPS01R' and Spell_Core_HRG is either 'SB97Z' or 'SC97Z'. Updated to ' where NCBLocal_Spell_Flag is ', NCBFinal_Spell_Flag is ' and NCBLocal_RuleApplied is anything but ''Military Practice (RRU)'.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Indicates whether the currency to be used for the activity is 'spell', as defined by the prescribed specialised services (PSS) identification tool.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: When the overall spell is classed as specialised then ' is applied; where an episode within the spell is specialised but the spell as a whole is not, then a ' is applied, and if there are no specialised service provided in the entire spell, then left null. All specialised classification is derived using the PSS tool of the relevant year.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Error messages as produced by the prescribed specialised services (PSS) identification tool. (based on all underlying episode records).
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Shows the first 2,500 characters of any error messages that are produced when passing the data through the PSS tool.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The generated record ID (SUS FCE identifier) of the underlying 'reporting' episode as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
A unique identifier for each spell assigned as part of the local payment HRG grouper.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Indicates whether the 'spell' has been identified as specialised activity as produced by the prescribed specialised services (PSS) identification tool.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Set as '1' when either the SpellServiceLine for the spell is complete, or the ServiceLine for an episode is complete, otherwise set as '0'. Derived using the PSS tool.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The grouping method used for the spell as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The grouping method used by the local payment grouper for the spell. Will either be ' (procedure driven), ' (diagnosis driven), ' (multiple trauma), ' (global exception), or null.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Adjustment to account for specialised service top up tariffs.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: When Cost_Type starts with 'Tariff', Specialised_TopUp_Indicator is ' and Spell_SSC is complete, the sum total of Tariff_Initial_Amount, Tariff_BestPrac_Adj, Tariff_ShortStay_Adj and Tariff_LongStay_Adj is multiplied by the TopUp_Rate which is taken from the Specialised Services Tariff reference table. This figure is then rounded to 2 decimal places. When Cost_Type starts with 'Tariff' and Spell_SSC contains '97' then 828 is added to the previous total. A default value of ' is applied when Cost_Type starts with 'Tariff' and Tariff_SpecServ_Adj is null.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The best practice tariff code list for the attendance as produced by the local payment HRG grouper (not currently populated within the NCDR).
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
Combines all best practice tariff codes generated by the local payment HRG grouper. (from five separate data fields prior to load) for each attendance into one field.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The spell programme budgeting category (PBC) produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
Takes the spell programme budget category from the outcomes of the local payment HRG grouper.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The outpatient procedure HRG on which procedure tariffs are applied.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The HRG code where an outpatient procedure has been grouped to an HRG.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The outpatient attendance HRG on which the attendance tariffs are applied.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The HRG code where an outpatient procedure has not been used to group to an HRG.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The trim point associated with the HRG.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
When the spell has an associated HRG code, a Calc_Type of 'Tariff' and Cost_Type is null, the following rules determine which trim point type is selected from a tariff reference table:
When Der_Management_Type is RDA or RNA and HRG_Code is'SB97Z'or'SC97Z'then Inpatient_Longstay_Trimpoint is used, this is also applied when Der_Management_Type is DC or EL.
When Der_Management_Type is EM or NE, NonElective_LongStay_TrimPoint is used.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Concatenated string detailing the reason/s as to why the spell has not been grouped using the local payment HRG grouper, e.g. '=' sign convention, well babies, etc. (based on all grouped underlying episode records).
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: The first 1,000 characters of the field Der_PreGrp_All which describes why a spell was not passed through the appropriate local payment HRG grouper.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Reason as to why the episode has not been grouped using the local payment HRG grouper, e.g. '=' sign convention, well babies etc.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The record is run through the HRG grouper for the relevant year, and the first 50 characters of the Exclusion_Reason are taken from the output table.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Reason as to why the attendance has not been grouped using the local payment HRG grouper, e.g. '=' Sign Convention, mental health services etc.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
When the last character in Commissioning_Serial_Number.
Set as '' Sign Convention' when the final character in Commissioning_Serial_Number is '.
Set as 'Cystic Fibrosis' when Treatment_Function_Code is '343' or '264'.
Set as 'Intermediate Care' when Treatment_Function_Code is '318'.
Set as 'Learning Disabilities' when Treatment_Function_Code is '700'.
Set as 'Mental Health Services' when Treatment_Function_Code is one of '710', '711', '712', '713', '715', '720', '721', '722', '723', '724', '725', '726' or '727'.
Set as 'Respite Care' when Treatment_Function_Code is '319'.
Set as 'NSCG Services' when Commissioner_Code is 'YDD82'.
Set as 'Private Patients' when Administrative_Category is '02'.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Unbundled HRGs as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The record is run through the HRG grouper for the relevant year, and the UnbundledHRGs field is taken from the output table.
For full details of the HRG Grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/article/2580/HRG4-201314-Local-Payment-Grouper
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Indicates whether the currency to be used for the activity is 'spell', as defined by the prescribed specialised services (PSS) identification tool.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Set as NCBPST_Spell_Currency where NCBPST_Spell_Flag is ', NCBFinal_Spell_Flag is ' and either: NCBPST_Spell_ServiceLine is anything but 'NCBPS01C' or'NCBPS01R', or NCBPST_Spell_ServiceLine is 'NCBPS01C' or 'NCBPS01R' and Spell_Core_HRG is 'SB97Z' or 'SC97Z'.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The dominant procedure used for procedure based grouping as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The flag code list for the attendance as produced by the 2017/18 local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
Combines all flag codes generated by the local payment HRG grouper (from five separate data fields prior to load) for each attendance into one field.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The grouping method used for the attendance as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The grouping method used by the local payment HRG grouper for the appointment. Will either be ' (procedure driven), ' (global exception) or null.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The specialised service code list for the attendance as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
Combines all specialised service codes generated by the local payment HRG grouper (from five separate data fields prior to load) for each attendance into one field.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The specialised service code used to adjust the cost of the spell (i.e. where any conditionality is met).
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
Spell_SSC is assigned according to a hierarchy, i.e. it will only show one 4 character code even if it meets two of the rules outlined below, and this will be the first one listed.
1) Set as 'SS93' when Spell_SSC_Key contains 'SS93' and the relevant record in the Specialised Services Inpatient Tariff reference table has a Spell_SSC of 'SS93' and Der_Age_at_CDS_Activity_Date is under 19.
2) Set as 'SS91' when Spell_SSC_Key contains 'SS91' and the relevant record in the Specialised Services Inpatient Tariff reference table has a Spell_SSC of 'SS91' and Der_Age_at_CDS_Activity_Date is under 19.
3) Set as ?SS06? when Spell_SSC_Key contains 'SS06' and the relevant record in the Specialised Services Inpatient Tariff reference table has a Spell_SSC of 'SS06'.
4) Set as ?SS08? when Spell_SSC_Key contains 'SS08' and the relevant record in the Specialised Services Inpatient Tariff reference table has a Spell_SSC of 'SS08' and Der_Age_at_CDS_Activity_Date is greater than or equal to 19.
5) Set as 'SS34' when Spell_SSC_Key contains 'SS34' and Der_Age_at_CDS_Activity_Date is equal to or greater than 19.
6) Set as 'SS97' when HRG_Code is either 'AA22A' or 'AA22B' and Spell_Unbundled_HRGs contains 'XD07Z'.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Unbundled HRGs as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
Any and all unbundled HRGs generated by the local payment HRG grouper.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The treatment function code for the spell as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: The same treatment function code as for the reporting episode within the spell.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The spell length of stay, adjusted in accordance with national tariff payment system rules & guidance.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: The sum of Der_Episode_Adj_LoS for each episode within the spell where FCE_Group_Status is 'Inc'.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The best practice code used to adjust the cost of the spell (i.e. where any conditionality is met).
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Set by looking up the best practice code in the appropriate reference table.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Adjustment to account for best practice tariffs.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Set to ' when Tariff_Exclusion_Reason is incomplete and Cost_Type is 'Tariff'. No rules beyond this have yet been developed.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Concatenated string of all of the best practice tariff code(s) for the spell as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
A concatenation of all best practice tariff codes for the spell, as derived by the appropriate HRG grouper.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The base national tariff.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
When Der_Management_Type is:
1) DC and Daycase_Tariff is complete in the HRG reference table then Daycase_Tariff is used.
2) EL and Inpatient_Tariff is complete in the HRG reference table then Inpatient_Tariff is used.
3) DC or EL and Elective_Tariff is complete in the HRG reference table then Elective_Tariff used.
4) RDA or RNA and HRG_Code is either'SB97Z'or'SC97Z'then Elective_Tariff is used.
5) EM or NE then NonElective_Tariff in the HRG reference table is used.
Only applied when Calc_Type is 'Tariff', HRG_Code is complete and Cost_Type is incomplete.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The long stay rate (per day unit rate) for excess bed days.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: The same value as LongStay_Day_Tariff in the HRG Reference Table. Only applied when Cost_Type starts with 'Tariff' and Spell_ExcessBedDays is greater than '. Set to ' where the above rule was not met and Cost_Type starts with 'Tariff'.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The dominant procedure used for procedure based grouping, as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The record is run through the HRG grouper for the relevant year, and the FCE_Dominant_Procedure is taken from the output table.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The base national tariff where the procedure tariff is applicable.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
When Tariff_Exclusion_Reason and Cost_Type are null, this field is set equal to the OP_Procedure_Tariff in the HRG Reference Table.
Set as ' where Tariff_Exclusion_Reason is incomplete, Tariff_OPP was not completed using the above rule and Tariff_Specialty is complete.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The dominant procedure using for procedure based grouping as produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
Derived according to the rules of the HRG grouper of the appropriate year.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The base national tariff where the specialty tariff is applicable.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: When Tariff_Exclusion_Reason and Cost_Type are null, Der_Staff_Type is 'Cons' and Der_Contact_Type is 'F2F' then the following rules are adhered to, otherwise this is left null. When HRG_Code_Other is 'WF01B' then the Cons_Single_First_Tariff (from the TFC Reference Table) is applied, when it is 'WF01A' then Cons_Single_FollowUp_Tariff is applied, when it is 'WF02B' then Cons_Multi_First_Tariff, when 'WF02A' then Cons_Multi_FollowUp_Tariff. Set as ' where Tariff_Exclusion_Reason and Tariff_Specialty are incomplete and Tariff_OPP is complete.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Concatenated string of all of the episode level error messages as produced by the local payment HRG grouper (based on all grouped underlying episode records).
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The first 2,500 characters of the Der_HRG_Err_All field which is an output of the HRG grouper for the appropriate year.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The spell HRG produced by the local payment HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
Derived according to the rules of the HRG grouper of the appropriate year.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Primary key - Use this field to join to the other tbl_Data_SEM_AEA_* tables.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: A unique integer assigned to the record in sequential order. Does not represent any information about the patient.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: An identifier on the raw data, i.e. assigned by NHS Digital prior to import to the NCDR, used during loading and processing.

Description: An identifier assigned during loading to aid processing.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: An identifier assigned in sequential order to each load file during processing. Does not represent any information about the patient.
Author: Amy Hutton

NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: A unique integer assigned to the record in sequential order. Does not represent any information about the patient.

Description: The local service line for the attendance, including values submitted by the provider for Provider Supplied flagged activity.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Runs through a hierarchy of rules; if one rule has already been met, all proceeding rules are not applied.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: A code to identify the format and basis of the release of an NHS organisation code being used. Not completed in the NCDR.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The local NPoC for the attendance, including values derived from the service line submitted by the provider for Provider Supplied flagged activity. (not relevant for A&E).
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Not populated for A&E. For OP - where this is not complete, concatenates NPoC_Category from the three NPoC tables used in processing where NCBLocal_Flag is complete and the first three characters of Commissioner_Code are a Commissioning Hub Code, a Local Area Team Code (that isn't 'Q99'), 'X24' or 'XMB'. Also adds this concatenation of fields where NCBLocal_RuleApplied contains '|Provider Submitted' and NCBLocal_ServiceLine is not complete. When NCBLocal_Flag is completed set as 'B03' where Attend_Core_HRG is 'SB97Z' and 'B01' where Attend_Core_HRG is 'SC97Z'.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: The service line code produced by (1) the PSS identification tool (national) and (2) locally derived direct commissioning rules.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Set as 'NCB_Milit' when NCBLocal_RuleApplied contains ''Military Personnel' and NCBLocal_RuleApplied does not contain '- RRU', otherwise leave null.
Author: Amy Hutton

Description: Error messages as produced by the 2016/17 reference costs HRG grouper.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology:
The record is run through the 2016/17 reference costs HRG grouper, and the first 1,000 characters of the Error_Message field are taken from the output table.
For full details of the HRG grouper, see NHS Digital's documentation:
http://content.digital.nhs.uk/casemix

Description: Records the sequence in which the baby was born, with 1 indicating the first or only birth in the sequence (i.e. singleton), 2 indicating the second birth in the sequence, 3 indicating the third, and so on.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The method by which a baby is delivered, which is a registrable birth.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: Records a period of between 10 to 49 weeks in completed weeks that is a clinical assessment of gestation length in weeks.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: Records the means by which regular respiration of the baby was attempted. This is not recorded for stillbirths. For local purposes, the actual drugs administered should be specified.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: This is normally the status of the individual who delivers the baby. When the delivery is carried out by a student, the individual supervising the delivery should be the one recorded as conducting it. This may be different for each birth in a multiple birth.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: A number used to identify a patient uniquely within a Health care Provider. It may be different from the patient's case note number and may be assigned automatically by the computer system.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: A code to identify the format and basis of the release of an NHS organisation code, in this case the organisation code of the provider which assigned the local patient identifier.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The organisation code of the organisation that assigned the local patient identifier.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The trace status of the NHS number (baby).
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The birth weight, where the unit of measurement is 'grams (g)'.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: An indication of whether the birth was a live or still birth.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The gender of a person. Person stated gender code is self declared or inferred by observation for those unable to declare their person stated gender.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The type of location for the birth.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: A classification for use within commissioning data set messages of the physical location within which the recorded patient event occurs. Recorded for the delivery place.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The actual place type of delivery.

Description: An indication of whether a critical care period was initiated as a result of a non-emergency treatment plan, for example, for elective major surgery. This relates only to the period of critical care and not to the nature of the hospital admission. For example, a planned hospital admission may unexpectedly require an emergency intensive care unit admission, in which case the classification will be '01'.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The total number of days that the patient received gastro-intestinal system support during a critical care period, ranging from 000 to 997 days.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The maximum number of organ systems supported on any one day during a critical care period. Each organ system can only be counted once on any calendar day. Both basic and advanced categories cannot be counted at the same time. The number of organ systems supported can be between 00 to 07, although for the purposes of recording on the commissioning data set messages gastro-intestinal support days are not recorded so the maximum is effectively 06.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The MFF payment for the activity.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: The sum total of Tariff_Initial_Amount, Tariff_BestPrac_Adj, Tariff_ShortStay_Adj, Tariff_LongStay_Adj and Tariff_SpecServ_Adj is multiplied by the MFF_Rate which is taken from the MFF reference table.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: Concatenated string indicating the local rule/s applied to identify direct commissioning activity.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Concatenated string indicating the local rule/s applied to identify direct commissioning activity.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: The code of an ambulance service which conveys a patient on a patient transport journey. A patient journey number and ambulance incident number may be recorded for the patient transport journey.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: CCG code based on lookup of SUS derived (PDS) GP practice code. Uses CCG reference data as of April 2017 for data from 2015/16 onwards.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Derived by looking up against the SUS-derived GP practice code.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: CCG code based on lookup of provider supplied GP practice code. Uses CCG reference data as of April 2017 for data from 2015/16 onwards.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Derived by looking up against the provider-submitted GP practice code.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: CCG code based on lookup of patient postcode. Uses CCG reference data as of April 2017 for data from 2015/16 onwards.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Derived by looking up against the patient's postcode.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: CCG code based on lookup of provider postcode (Host CCG). Uses CCG reference data as of April 2017 for data from 2015/16 onwards.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Derived by looking up against the provider's postcode.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description:
Final CCG code based on following logic:
 Historic Activity (prior to current financial year): First of
  SUS_GP_Practice_CCG, Patient_Postcode_CCG and Provider_Postcode_CCG
Current Activity (current financial year): First of
  Provider_GP_Practice_CCG, Patient_Postcode_CCG and Provider_Postcode_CCG.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Historic Activity (prior to current financial year): First of; SUS_GP_Practice_CCG, Patient_Postcode_CCG and Provider_Postcode_CCG.' current Activity ' current financial year): First of; Provider_GP_Practice_CCG, Patient_Postcode_CCG and Provider_Postcode_CCG.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: An identifier to distinguish between the CC files during the load process.

Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: Indicates whether the record contains any patient confidential data in free text fields. Any PCD is removed from the text fields and replaced with a marker within the string, e.g. if an NHS number is found this is replaced with the text "_<NHS_No>_".
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: Prior to pseudonymisation and publication, eight free text fields Unique_CDS_Identifier,Unique_Booking_Reference_Number_Converted, Local_Patient_ID, Patient_Pathway_ID, Provider_Reference_Number, Commissioner_Reference_Number, Agreement_Line_Number, Attendance_Identifier) are scanned for NHS number, Postcode and Date of Birth of the patient. If PCD is found in any of these fields, the patient confidential data held within that field is stripped and replaced with a marker ('_<NHS_No>_', _<PC_' or '_<DoB_') and the record is flagged with a in CC_PCD_Indicator.
Author: Nathan Abbotts

Description: Used to distinguish between occurrences within the same _Ident.
NCDR_Derivation_Methodology: A unique integer assigned to the record in sequential order, within the same _Ident. Does not represent any information about the patient.
Author: Nathan Abbotts
